ExtraDataReader Class Reference

Objects of this class will read an asciifile with extra data (map correction records) that will be inserted into the mcm map after it is created from the map supplier data but before it is added to the running mc2-system. More...

Handle the records.
The methods that are called to handle the different recordtypes.

Almost all methods have the exact same parameters.

Parameters:
recStr A vector with the tokens of this record in strings.
parseOnly If this parameter is set, only the syntax of the record will be checked (nothing will be changed on the map).
Returns:
True if the syntax of the record is correct (parseOnly == true) or if the item is added to the map (parseOnly == false). False will be returned if the syntax of the record is wrong (parseOnly == true), or if the item not was added to the current map (parseOnly == false).

Attributes from COMMENT record.
Attributes extraced from the extra data record comment, used either when checking extra data validity or when applying dynamic extra data.

  • uint32 m_recordId
    The id of the extra data record beeing processed, extracted from the COMMENT.
  • MC2String m_originalValStr
    The original value for the extra data record beeing processed, extracted from the COMMENT.
  • MC2String m_edInsertType
    The extra data insert type for the extra data record beeing processed, extracted from the COMMENT.
  • MC2String m_recordEDdate
    The extra data record date-and-time for the extra data record beeing processed, extracted from the COMMENT.
Vectors for dynamic extra data.
Vectors used, when applying dynamic extra data to merged maps, for saving node/item ids in the underview map beeing processed for after-processing.

The vectors are however filled regardless of the m_applyOnMergedMaps attribute.

  • vector< uint32 > m_affectsTurnDescr
    m_affectsTurnDescr Contains nodeIds of the nodes where turn descriptions need to be re-generated.
  • vector< uint32 > m_affectsStreets
    m_affectsStreets Contains itemIds of those street segment items whose name(s) have been changed and require streets to be re-generated.
  • vector< uint32 > m_affectsMap
    m_affectsMap Contains itemIds of all other items that have changed due to a map error correction.

Static Private Attributes

  • const uint32 NBRS_OF_CHECK_COORD_INSIDE_BUA
    Number of times to generate random coordinates and check if they are inside a BuiltUpArea-item in the ADD_CITYPART-function.

Detailed Description

Objects of this class will read an asciifile with extra data (map correction records) that will be inserted into the mcm map after it is created from the map supplier data but before it is added to the running mc2-system.

bool ExtraDataReader::applyCurrentRecordDynamic (   )  [private]
 

Find out if m_mapEDdate is less than m_recordEDdate, to decide if a record should be applied when running dynamic extra data.

An extra data record that is older than the m_mapEDdate was (most likely) applied in an earlier dynamic extra data parsing, and should not be re-applied.

Returns:
True if the record comment date is more resent than the map-date and should be applied, false if the record is old and should not be applied.

void ExtraDataReader::checkAndAddMapCandidate (  ItemTypes::itemType  it,
int32  lat,
int32  lon,
uint32  recId
)  [private]
 

Check if this map is a candidate for a certain record.

Used for finding map candidates for missing-records. If any item of itemtype it is close to the coordinate given (within 500 meters) the map is a candidate, and the mapID is added to the record's mapIdCandidates-vector.

bool ExtraDataReader::handleCommentRecord (  vector< MC2String > &  recStr,
bool  parseOnly
)  [private]
 

Handle one COMMENT-record.

When checking extra data, the extra data record id and original value are extracted and saved in membervariables. When applying dynamic extra data, the extra data insert type and comment date-and-time are likewise extracted and saved. Record defintion:

  1. # Date and Time
  2. Writer
  3. Source
  4. Comment
  5. Original value
  6. Ref id (map supplier map error ref id)
  7. Extra data record id
  8. Extra data insert type
  9. OldMap supplier and release
  10. Extra data group id (if any)
  11. Country
  12. OldMap id

bool ExtraDataReader::initCheckTable (   ) 
 

Initiate the check table when checking extra data.

Pre-reads the extra data file and stores information about the records in the table based on extra data record id. The table is further filled with info when running the parseInto-method with the m_checkRecords variable set to true, storing e.g. whether a record is found in the map or not, still needed or not, etc.

The extra data types that can be checked includes:

  1. ADD_NAME_TO_ITEM
  2. ADD_SIGNPOST
  3. REMOVE_ITEM
  4. REMOVE_NAME_FROM_ITEM
  5. REMOVE_POIS
  6. REMOVE_SIGNPOST
  7. SET_CONTROLLEDACCESS
  8. SET_ENTRYRESTRICTIONS
  9. SET_HOUSENUMBER
  10. SET_LEVEL
  11. SET_MULTIDIGITISED
  12. SET_RAMP
  13. SET_ROUNDABOUT
  14. SET_ROUNDABOUTISH
  15. SET_SPEEDLIMIT
  16. SET_TOLLROAD
  17. SET_TURNDIRECTION
  18. SET_VEHICLERESTRICTIONS
  19. SET_WATER_TYPE
  20. UPDATE_NAME

bool ExtraDataReader::printCheckTable (   ) 
 

Print information from the extra data check table after running the parseInto-method, resulting in different outfiles with:.

  1. extra data records that are not checked.
  2. extra data records that are found in the map and still needed for correction.
  3. extra data records that are found in the map but not needed for correction.
  4. extra data records that are found in the map and where the attribute value does not match with the original value given in the comment. Duplicates to these records exist in the other two found-files.
  5. extra data records that are not found in any of the looped maps. The main reason for the record to be missing is a change in geometry. However for theese records a candidate map id is most likely found.

Definition at line 843 of file ExtraDataReader.h.

bool ExtraDataReader::m_applyOnMergedMaps [private]
 

Tells if the extra data records are applied on underview maps of a merge, so called dynamic extra data.

The meber variable is set to true in the initMergedMaps function, false otherwise.

When applying dynamic extra data, for each record the comment date is checked against the extra data date of the map, so no old records are applied. IDs of all items affected by any record are saved in vectors or other containers during the parsing. The changes are then by other methods applied also to overview- and country overview maps, all levels.
